\f1\b \cf2 The B Word ::
\f0\b0 \
\
I couldn't believe I said it. It was one of the worst things I could speak to my wife. We were in an argument and it just slipped out...the B word. Now before you put down the book I need to give some back story. Lisa and I had been married for a little while now and I knew what to say to push her buttons.\
\
Normally I'm pretty controlled in what I say and don't say but this fight was different. I was angry and wanted to play a little dirty to really show her. A few months earlier she had told there was one word I had used in the past that really bothered her when we fought and it was this word...the word she asked me to never say to her again...BITTER.\
\
Yep, that's the B word in our household. What B word were you thinking of? For Lisa, it's pretty much the worst thing I can call her. This is a bunch of history behind why i shouldn't say it. I had told her I wouldn't use it again but it slipped through. I had spent several months fighting off the urges and controlling my tongue like the Bible tells me to. But this night..it just sort of slipped through the filter.\
\
And that is what we all have to control our behaviors. Filters. We know what we should do and shouldn't do. We do our best to control those urges and desires to say or do something we know deep down we shouldn't...until it slips through. \
\
Yours may not be how you talk but what you eat or drink. It could be what you look at when no is watching you. It could be a behavior you know is wrong but every now and then you give in. You are not even sure why because you don't really want to do it. But you do.\
\
\

