\f0\b0\fs24 \nosupersub \'93Are you still so dull?\'94\'a0Jesus asked them.\'a0
\f1\b\fs20 \super 17\'a0
\f0\b0\fs24 \nosupersub \'93Don\'92t you see that whatever enters the mouth goes into the stomach and then out of the body?\'a0
\f1\b\fs20 \super 18\'a0
\f0\b0\fs24 \nosupersub But the things that come out of a person\'92s mouth come from the heart,\'a0and these defile them.\'a0
\f1\b\fs20 \super 19\'a0
\f0\b0\fs24 \nosupersub For out of the heart come evil thoughts\'97murder, adultery, sexual immorality, theft, false testimony, slander.\'a0
\f1\b\fs20 \super 20\'a0
\f0\b0\fs24 \nosupersub These are what defile a person;\'a0but eating with unwashed hands does not defile them.\'94\
\
Jesus essentially says the Pharisees have it all wrong. They are focused on keeping the external clean. Making sure everything looks good on the outside. The problem is what is on the inside eventually is going to slip through the filter and come out. \
\
If I were to look back at what I said to Lisa, it was a heart problem. I wanted to win an argument more than I wanted to honor my wife. I wanted to get even and make sure I took her down in the process. It would have been easy in the moment to apologize and act like I wasn't sure where that came from. But I knew, she knew. It was my heart. Because of my heart comes the things I say.\
\
Thankfully that is no longer and issue in our marriage but it isn't because I have a new and improved 2.0 filter to protect her from all the things I wish I could say. It's because over the years I've worked on that area of my life. I do absolutely have filters, there's nothing wrong with them, but I no longer rely on those to protect me.\
\
\
(I tried to control my behavior instead of all God to heal my heart...there i's a huge difference!)\
\
I even thought to myself "Where did that come from?"...but I knew. I knew exactly where it came from...my heart.\'a0 \
\
Let me tell you what this book won't be about. It won't be about a bunch of behaviors that you should or should not do. This is religion and is the exact opposite of what we are looking for. We are looking to help transform our hearts and minds so not only do our behaviors change but also our desires.\
\
\
\
Concept of 'where did that come from'...inside of your heart.\
\
Romans 12:1,2\
Jesus and where our sin comes from - what comes out of us not into us.\
Guard your heart for out of it is the wellspring of life\
\
\'a0We want to be different without behaving different but what separates us from others is not our gifting but our preparation.\'a0\
